file: prompts/summarizer-rollup.md
behavior: Defines the prompt template used to generate `rollup.ctx` for a directory, instructing an LLM to summarize a subtree's domain, cross-child coupling, and per-child roles from the parent's perspective for consumption by other LLMs under context budget.
edit_notes:
  - Companion to prompts/summarizer-leaf.md (per-file `.ctx` generation); the two prompts must stay consistent on tone, banned-phrase list, and "facts only" philosophy since rollups sit above leaf summaries in the same context tree.
  - The 15-line target / 40-line ceiling is stated here but is sourced from docs/SPEC.md (rule 10); changing the budget must be done in SPEC.md first, not by editing this prompt alone.
  - Output format is strict: no code fences, no markdown headings, exact section order (directory/domain/edit_notes/children/invariants/intent_divergence) — downstream parsing likely depends on this shape.
  - `intent_divergence:` is the only line that is conditionally omitted; every other section header must be emitted even when empty.
functions:
invariants:
  - The example output block always ends with a divergence line to illustrate rule 5; the prompt's own instructions require omitting that line when no divergence exists.
external_deps: to fill in later, if any deps identified in the file exist